<strong>The post-steel ladder</strong>

<strong>Mithril</strong> — first metal above steel. Requires a steel pickaxe to mine. Melts in an adamantite <a href="crucible">crucible</a> or better. Full tool and armor coverage. Mithril rods and plates are the prerequisite for crafting an adamantite crucible shell.

<strong>Adamantite</strong> — mid-game endgame. Requires a mithril pickaxe. Melts in an adamantite crucible (its native tier). Adamantite is the prerequisite for the dragon crucible shell.

<strong>Runite</strong> — rare high-tier. Requires an adamantite pickaxe. Cannot be melted in the adamantite crucible — only the dragon crucible reaches runite temperature. (Or add a <a href="superheater">superheater</a>.)

<strong>Dragon</strong> — the absolute ceiling. Requires a runite pickaxe (or a runic pickaxe if Rune-Story is loaded). Only the dragon crucible can melt it. Required for dragon weapons and their special attacks.

<strong>Where to look</strong>
Depths increase with tier. Grade ladder is the vanilla poor → medium → rich → bountiful; grade governs yield, not tier.

<strong>Compare</strong>
Plate versus <a href="lamellae">lamellar</a>: plate has slightly higher raw absorption; lamellar has better relative-protection scaling and lighter weight per piece.
